<br>Several Backpacks filled with Bandages<br><br><b>Zone:</b><br>Lavastorm<br><br><b>What you do:</b><br><br>Head over to lavastorm, and take what I like to call a "Lava Bath". You wander into a puddle or pool of lava taking non-melee damage until your health falls to about half a bubble or so (Reminder: Keep mend up just incase you run into a lil' nasty that attacks you. Any aggressive MoB will attack you if your hurt bad enough!) then hope out and begin to bind. As childish and seemingly pointless as it is. I was able to take my bind would from 75 to almost 185 in almost 2 hours. I mean with over 1200 bandages I flw though them but my skill went up almsot every other bind with an intelligence of 95 (I had a few pieces of cheap gear on like +2INT rings, and a Robe of the Oracles). Well thats basically my guide, you simply repeat until your skill hits its cap, and you go about your way.<br><br>I knwo its not the greatest guide in the world for increasing skill, but it works, and its faster then letting/risking a mob beat on you 'til near death. Well, I hope this helps some of you monks that were a little lacking in the bind wound department. Good luck! <p><b>Paio Fyrefury</b><br>Lv. 36 Human Monk<br>Erollisi Marr<br>Blades of Honor<br><br>"I know the pieces fit, 'cause I watched them fall away" ~Tool~ <i>Schizm</i>, Lateralus<br><br> "In the waning moon, a soft pillar of light entrances the hope of a broken soul" ~Paio Fyrefury~ (Me)</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ubodikibadachi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BodiKibadachi</A> at: 1/25/02 6:00:19 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ukazuke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kazuke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/18/01 8:32:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=480.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A simple, and easy way to increase bind wound.</span><hr size=1> Good idea, just make sure your high enough so you dont get agro'd by the imps and such. I believe the Gypsie vendors in Lavastorm sell bandages even, so you can just &quot;bathe&quot; near them. Personaly i preferred killing two birds with one stone, and practiced bind wound while practicing safe fall, places like dagnor's cauldron were great for it. Just grab a sow from someone before hand. Or heck, use the wall of the zone to Nektulos on EC side, and you can buy/sell at the same time.<br><br>Kazuke Omonojawku<br>Disciple of Quellious<br>-Mystique Alliance-<br>Torvonillous server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ukeyeluke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keyeluke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/19/01 5:44:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=480.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A simple, and easy way to increase bind wound.</span><hr size=1> Gypsy vendors do indeed sell bandages.  I used to use them to sell stuff and cash out coins when hunting SolB.  Take some lava baths, bandage up, repeat.  Took a LOT of bandaids to get to 200 - I got stuck on 189 and on 194 (200+ each).  At 51 I got to 201 and 70% bind wound with 63 bandaids and 75 INT.  One of the greatest skills monks get, IMO.  If you have a mage and a shammy in your group, you can get your shammy to full mana and 70 HP in a hurry.  Between mobs, get some summoned bandages, and have the shammy cannibalize while you bind him up.<br><br>Also good for power-leveling <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Stand behind your twink and bandage him while he fights red mobs - when mob gets to half health, finish it off, rinse, repeat. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ukhran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/01 6:20:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=480.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> Tie in sneak and sense heading too.<br><br>Say your bind wound is in ability slot one, sneak 2, and sense heading 4.<br><br>make a hot button that goes.<br><br>/doability 1<br>/doability 2 (to turn on sneak)<br>/doability 2 (again to turn it off)<br>/doabilty 4 <br><br>Thats what my bind wound hotboutton looks anyway. So, you could be raising more then just one skill.<br><br>Thats a good spot to raise that skill, I usually raise my by soloing.<br><br>k <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ulyberniabelisama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lybernia Belisama</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.sherilyn.net/misc/sherry.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/01 6:24:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=480.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.sherilyn.net/sigs/lyb2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A simple, and easy way to increase bind wound.</span><hr size=1> Personally I think it makes more sense to raise bind wound at the same time as safe fall.  Just find a nice place to jump off of and take damage.  I used the ramp in fv that leads to the temple area.  Takes about 45 damage max, works up safe fall, and allows you to bind wound with bandages for sale near by.  No mobs to worry about either.   <p><img src=http://www.sherilyn.net/sigs/lybmauv.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/udevlashadowsoul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Devla Shadowsoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/20/01 8:24:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=480.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ozemail.com.au/~snowsoq/skull.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A simple, and easy way to increase bind wound.</span><hr size=1> My recommendations...<br><br>Lava bath is the best way I have found for BW increases.  Donate some cash to a friendly Mage, and have him summon you his 10 slot 100% WR bags filled with bandages (saves you spending any of your precious supply of cash).<br><br>Then use the Erudin TP gems trick for Safe Fall.  I let Safe Fall slide for a few levels (is 185/200 at the moment) then get a port over there.  Set up the run and go AFK <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Regards,<br><br>CJ<br> <p>Devla    - 51 Dark Elf Heretic<br>Morin    - 37 Human Monk<br><p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>