span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uljfong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ljfong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/30/01 2:28:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=480.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A simple, and easy way to increase bind wound.</span><hr size=1> I also found it also very easy to increase bind wound/safe fall at the mountain road from high pass hold to eastern karana. Basically just walk till you are at the eastern karana end of the mountain road and start judging how high you can afford falling without actually dying. The advantage is, at this place you can kinda choose how high and how painful the fall you want it to be. You can choose some pretty good steep climbs so you average about 5-7 falling animations each time you make the run downs, I got my safe fall from 105 to 161 in reasonable amount of time as well as bind wounds.<br><br>Shinhan<br>44th level Monk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uzolina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zolina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/31/01 9:20:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=480.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A simple, and easy way to increase bind wound.</span><hr size=1> Just find any mid-green mob, attack it once, and keep sitting down so it hits you for maximum damage.  Let it beat you down to one bubble or so, then kill it, bind wounds as far as you can, and repeat.  You can do this in almost any zone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/upaiothemonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paio the Monk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/4/01 5:31:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=480.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A simple, and easy way to increase bind wound.</span><hr size=1> Yes, all good ideas. Yet mid-green mobs can sometimes call upopn the aid of others when they run and your health sinks a little too low. Feign Death won't save you then... but nor will it when you do the same with lava, its a toss up really, and a risk vs. reward (in this case, skill capping) sorta deal, no? <p><b><a href="mailto:paio_the_monk@hotmail.com">Paio Fyrefury</a></b><br>Lv. 48 Human Monk<br>Erollisi Marr<br><a href="http://www.geocities.com/bladesofhonor">Blades of Honor (Officer)</a><br><br><b>Dragons:</b>(win/loss)<br>Lord Nagafen: 1/0</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/uzurd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zurd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/4/01 6:16:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=480.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A simple, and easy way to increase bind wound.</span><hr size=1> Easiest way by far (and Much less dangerous) just be friends with your local shaman and have him donate an hour to you...he can cannibalize himself as you bandage (and no the casting doesnt interrupt the bandaging)  You just provide the bandages (or recruit a mage friend for that) and ZAP!  There 